FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1780405872
OL,3,CFamily 'will never forgive' hospital
OL,4,Cfor 'avoidable' death of grandmother
OL,6,FDuring a delay in the 76-year-old's
OL,7,Ftreatment, she contracted sepsis. The
OL,8,FPHSO found that earlier diagnoses and
OL,9,Fintervention would have saved her life.
OL,11,FSevinc Ulkueri was from Istanbul and
OL,12,Flived with her family in Solihull. She
OL,13,Fwas taken to the hospital in March
OL,14,F2021 after four days of vomiting,
OL,15,Fabdominal pain, shortness of breath
OL,16,Fand constipation.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1780405872
OL,3,CFamily 'will never forgive' hospital
OL,4,Cfor 'avoidable' death of grandmother
OL,6,FShe was seen at the hospital, given an
OL,7,FX-ray, and treated for pneumonia. The
OL,8,FX-ray indicated she might have further
OL,9,Fproblems, but it wasn't acted upon
OL,10,Funtil the following week.
OL,12,FThe watchdog found she was also given
OL,13,Fthe wrong advice and told to eat when
OL,14,Fshe shouldn't have been.
OL,16,FWhen she was eventually diagnosed,
OL,17,FSevinc Ulkueri had surgery, but
OL,18,Fshortly afterwards, she developed
OL,19,Fsepsis and died.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1780405872
OL,3,CFamily 'will never forgive' hospital
OL,4,Cfor 'avoidable' death of grandmother
OL,6,FSevinc Ulkueri's daughter Seniz
OL,7,FGreenhalgh said, "How could we have
OL,8,Fknown that when the ambulance took our
OL,9,Fbeloved mother to hospital she would
OL,10,Fnever come home?
OL,12,F"The intense pain, coupled with her
OL,13,Fvery limited English, meant she relied
OL,14,Fon me and my sister to communicate
OL,15,Fwith the medical team. They repeatedly
OL,16,Fignored or dismissed our pleas to take
OL,17,Fher abdominal pain seriously. Instead,
OL,18,Fthey repeatedly said her bowel was not
OL,19,Fblocked.
OL,26,@oD@ROUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1780405872
OL,3,CFamily 'will never forgive' hospital
OL,4,Cfor 'avoidable' death of grandmother
OL,6,F"Our loving mother's death was both
OL,7,Fpremature and completely avoidable. We
OL,8,Fwill never forgive the hospital for
OL,9,Fthe pain, fear, and suffering our
OL,10,Fmother endured, and for the lifelong
OL,11,Fgrief they have inflicted on our
OL,12,Ffamily."
OL,14,FRebecca Hilsenrath. The CEO of PHSO
OL,15,Fadded, "The failings in this case are
OL,16,Fsome that we see far too often.
OL,17,FDelayed reporting on scans,
OL,18,Finvestigations that are not
OL,19,Fsufficiently thorough, and poor
OL,20,Fcommunication with patients and their
OL,21,Ffamilies.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@HO]wD@HOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1780405872
OL,3,CFamily 'will never forgive' hospital
OL,4,Cfor 'avoidable' death of grandmother
OL,6,F"Sevinc was unable to clearly express
OL,7,Fthe severity and location of her pain
OL,8,Fbecause she was not given the support
OL,9,Fshe needed and to which she was
OL,10,Fentitled. Patients have a right to an
OL,11,Finterpreter and NHS services must be
OL,12,Faccessible to everyone in need of care.
OL,14,F"Listening to patients is crucial.
OL,15,FWhether in relation to their
OL,16,Ftreatment, or in the form of a
OL,17,Fcomplaint, the patient voice is
OL,18,Fcentral to safe and effective care."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOUzD@dO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/7
